1
00:00:00,537 --> 00:00:26,071
Namo Tassa Bhagavato Harahato Sambha Sambhudassa Namo Tassa Bhagavato Harahato Sambha Sambhudassa Namo Tassa Bhagavato Harahato Sambha Sambhudassa

2
00:00:26,710 --> 00:00:39,503
Homage to the Buddha, the Blessed, Noble and Fully Self-Awakened One.

3
00:00:39,523 --> 00:00:44,046
I want to look at this word asava, A-S-A-V-A.

4
00:00:44,067 --> 00:00:53,697
The V is always pronounced with a W. Let me start off by giving you the Pali text society dictionary definitions.

5
00:00:56,595 --> 00:00:58,459
And it gives you an idea of what they are.

6
00:01:00,142 --> 00:01:06,131
The first is an intoxicating extract or secretion from a tree or flower.

7
00:01:08,073 --> 00:01:09,436
A bit like opium or whatever.

8
00:01:09,876 --> 00:01:10,578
That's an asana.

9
00:01:12,019 --> 00:01:18,790
The second is it's used to describe, as the discharge of a sore.

10
00:01:20,813 --> 00:01:21,796
Discharge of a sore.

11
00:01:21,816 --> 00:01:24,459
It gives you another feel for the word.

12
00:01:25,704 --> 00:01:33,718
In psychology, it used to befuddle, I came across another word I'd never seen before, to befoozle.

13
00:01:36,382 --> 00:01:37,724
Befoozles the mind.

14
00:01:38,867 --> 00:01:48,001
And it's normally translated in terms of the Buddha Dhamma as cankers, taints, corruptions, intoxicants, biases.

15
00:01:49,745 --> 00:01:50,346
That's what they are.

16
00:01:52,250 --> 00:02:05,942
And later on, just to give us another idea of what they are, it seems that the word oga was used, O-G-H-A, which means a flood, floods.

17
00:02:06,742 --> 00:02:11,768
And even yoga, yoking, something that yokes you.

18
00:02:12,269 --> 00:02:15,371
So you've got a couple of images there.

19
00:02:15,390 --> 00:02:20,316
You've got things that are corruptions, intoxicants, that outflows, they're...

20
00:02:20,650 --> 00:02:24,756
Sometimes they're an influx, but I don't quite understand that.

21
00:02:24,776 --> 00:02:27,419
It's either an outflow or an influx, but anyway, maybe both.

22
00:02:28,461 --> 00:02:32,608
They flood the whole psychophysical organism.

23
00:02:33,329 --> 00:02:37,574
They yoke us, they tie us down, enslave us.

24
00:02:40,038 --> 00:02:41,199
They're corruptions.

25
00:02:43,364 --> 00:02:43,965
They're horrible.

26
00:02:46,627 --> 00:02:47,669
So what are they, is it?

27
00:02:48,544 --> 00:02:50,168
Well, they won't come as a surprise.

28
00:02:50,207 --> 00:02:51,530
The first one is kamma.

29
00:02:51,909 --> 00:02:55,455
That's not the same as kamma with a double M. That's sensual desire.

30
00:02:56,717 --> 00:02:58,842
Remember, it's not sensual desire in itself.

31
00:02:59,042 --> 00:03:03,229
It's always this relationship we have with sensual desire and seeking happiness there.

32
00:03:03,449 --> 00:03:04,330
That's the first one.

33
00:03:06,394 --> 00:03:07,475
The second one is bhava.

34
00:03:08,157 --> 00:03:09,919
So that's this becoming.

35
00:03:10,039 --> 00:03:15,649
So whereas sensual desire brings us into the present moment of wrong relationships,

36
00:03:16,591 --> 00:03:21,318
And we can also include in that sensual desire, remember, those things that we don't like.

37
00:03:23,419 --> 00:03:32,673
Normally this is translated as things that you do like, but I don't see why we can't also include things we don't like, because that brings out a negative desire, not wanting.

38
00:03:34,436 --> 00:03:41,264
But the Bhāva gives us this sensual desire of what happens to us in terms of time, passage of time, becoming.

39
00:03:42,932 --> 00:03:44,534
The third one is avijja.

40
00:03:44,555 --> 00:03:46,437
This is basic not knowing.

41
00:03:47,759 --> 00:03:48,640
Basic not knowing.

42
00:03:49,562 --> 00:03:53,048
And later on, it would seem, it was added, ditti was added.

43
00:03:53,147 --> 00:03:53,929
This is in the scriptures.

44
00:03:53,989 --> 00:04:00,117
It seems as though the three that we've mentioned, the sensitives are the becoming and the ignorance, were the original.

45
00:04:00,157 --> 00:04:06,647
Then, as the Buddha began to explain it more, he brought in this added ditti, which is wrong view.

46
00:04:08,530 --> 00:04:10,272
And wrong views, of course,

47
00:04:10,793 --> 00:04:14,336
are the product of this avijja, this ignorance.

48
00:04:14,457 --> 00:04:19,142
Ignorance, another word that we come across is moha, remember, this is that delusion.

49
00:04:19,363 --> 00:04:23,269
So the delusion is a consequence of ignorance.

50
00:04:23,288 --> 00:04:27,072
Often that's, I think, confused, but the one is prior to the other.

51
00:04:28,355 --> 00:04:34,423
Not so much prior in time, but the delusion arises out of an ignorance.

52
00:04:34,442 --> 00:04:35,704
And it produces these wrong views.

53
00:04:35,764 --> 00:04:37,206
So these wrong views

54
00:04:37,523 --> 00:04:40,767
are not to understand the Four Noble Truths.

55
00:04:41,889 --> 00:04:44,954
That is basic understanding.

56
00:04:44,975 --> 00:04:47,759
So that's what these āśvara are.

57
00:04:47,779 --> 00:04:56,173
Āśvara, kamma, which besends desire, bhāva, becoming, avijja, ignorance, and ditti, wrong views.

58
00:04:56,795 --> 00:05:07,348
And the reason that I've done them now is because of their connection to the we dependent origination, which is all about liberation.

59
00:05:07,769 --> 00:05:11,694
So this actually connects us to the paths and fruits.

60
00:05:12,916 --> 00:05:16,221
The first path and fruit, the sotapatti,

61
00:05:16,588 --> 00:05:19,533
the Sotapanna, the one who's attained first path and fruit.

62
00:05:21,055 --> 00:05:28,767
In the second path and fruit of the once-returner, the sense desire is lessened.

63
00:05:29,668 --> 00:05:33,314
It connects us with the non-returner and it connects us with the Arahant.

64
00:05:33,295 --> 00:05:43,350
So once we enter into the Sotapanna, the wrong views disappear, just the wrong views, misunderstanding, and there are three of them.

65
00:05:45,053 --> 00:05:59,978
This personality as a self, skeptical doubt, meaning that no doubt in the Buddha remains, the Buddhadhamma remains, and clinging to wrong rites and rituals, which is basically thinking that rites and rituals

66
00:06:00,312 --> 00:06:01,995
will help you become liberated.

67
00:06:02,314 --> 00:06:04,660
That's the clinging to wrong rites and rituals.

68
00:06:04,680 --> 00:06:15,899
Not that rites and rituals are wrong in themselves, they have their place, but it's when you think that they are material or essential for the process of liberation, that's when you've got a wrong view.

69
00:06:17,721 --> 00:06:24,514
When we get to the non-returner, the one that goes is kamma, the sense desire, seeking happiness in the sensual world.

70
00:06:25,725 --> 00:06:31,175
And the other two, the avijja, the ignorance, and the becoming, don't disappear until right at the end.

71
00:06:31,334 --> 00:06:32,798
So the self is always there.

72
00:06:33,658 --> 00:06:37,345
The becoming, remember, and the idea of self are synonymous.

73
00:06:37,444 --> 00:06:38,266
They mean the same thing.

74
00:06:40,690 --> 00:06:45,538
Self, in a way, doesn't get across the idea that it's continually changing.

75
00:06:45,778 --> 00:06:48,223
Our identities are continually changing.

76
00:06:48,675 --> 00:07:04,276
So often you'll hear writers or people use the word sell things to get across the idea that in fact we're constantly in this state of bhava, this state of becoming, which is a state of continuously renewing the idea of who we are.

77
00:07:05,999 --> 00:07:08,521
It's identity.

78
00:07:08,541 --> 00:07:18,615
So that concludes my little talk on the asava, the outflows, the influxes, the cankers, the taints, the corruptions, the intoxicants and the biases.

79
00:07:20,754 --> 00:07:22,877
Oh, that's something else I should mention, by the way.

80
00:07:23,278 --> 00:07:46,853
That whenever they're describing an Adahat, when somebody makes the full liberation, at the end of the point of becoming it, you'll read the scriptures and say something to the effect of, while listening, the hearts of the bhikkhus, or the hearts of those listening, were freed from the cankers through clinking no more.

81
00:07:47,855 --> 00:07:49,377
And

82
00:07:49,358 --> 00:07:53,646
That's one of the definitions of an Arahant.

83
00:07:54,086 --> 00:07:57,093
He's a kināsava, somebody who destroyed the kankas.

84
00:07:58,696 --> 00:08:13,324
May I hope that my words have been of some assistance and that you are liberated from all the āsava sooner rather than later.

